      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While high doses of vitamin D may boost your immune system, taking 50,000 IU daily for a few weeks is not recommended without consulting a healthcare professional first. Such high doses can cause side effects like nausea, vomiting, and increased liver enzyme levels. Furthermore, taking extremely high doses can also interfere with other nutrients' absorption and increase the risk of toxicity. A safe and effective approach would be to consult a doctor about getting regular vitamin D levels checked and adjusting the dosage accordingly.",
